    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Daimler-Benz Aerospace A.G. of Germany appealed to the Government yesterday for aid in weathering a financial crisis brought on by the strong mark. The company has said it will lose "hundreds of millions of marks" this year because most of its business is calculated in dollars while its production is in Germany, which means a weak dollar effectively raises the costs of production. The company had a loss of 438 million marks ($303 million) last year after losses of nearly 700 million ($484 million) at current rates the year before. (Reuters)</p>
      </block>
